sentences: Aska, Ryo Aska or Ryō Asuka (飛鳥 涼, Asuka Ryō) (born Shigeaki Miyazaki (宮﨑 重明, Miyazaki Shigeaki) on February 24, 1958 in Ono, Onojō, Fukuoka) is a Japanese singer-songwriter.
As a composer, he wrote most of the duo's hit songs, including "Morning Moon," "Love Song," "Say Yes," and "Meguriai."
He began a solo career in 1987, and was highly successful in the early 1990s.
He began a solo career in 1987, and was highly successful in the early 1990s.
He was arrested in May 2014 for possession of the illegal stimulant MDMA.
On September 12, 2014, he was sentenced to three years in prison suspended for four years.
